Third-party components (permissive, redistributed as part of the build):
  - thiserror (MIT OR Apache-2.0)           — align-core error types
  - proptest  (MIT OR Apache-2.0, dev only) — property tests
  - Tauri v2 and ecosystem (MIT OR Apache-2.0) — desktop shell
  - React (MIT), Vite (MIT)                 — frontend

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
External alignment tools are NOT bundled or linked. Iberalign detects and
invokes them as separate processes only when the user has installed them:
  - MAFFT          (BSD-like)  — default MSA engine, safe to bundle later
  - MUSCLE v5      (GPL)       — invoke-only; never linked or redistributed
  - Clustal Omega  (GPL)       — invoke-only; never linked or redistributed

Keeping GPL tools as separate, user-installed processes keeps Iberalign's own
code under a non-GPL license. See iberprime-spec.md §11.
